Dear white people referring to themselves as princex, 

I'm white. Let's get that out of the way. Born of a British man and an Irish woman, I am as white as can be. My grandparents are all white. My great grandparents are all white. I recognize how much of a benefit this is to me. I'm also nonbinary and (I'm a demigirl, partial female, partial neutrois).

Now that we've cleared that up, onto the meat of this:

Stop using the term princex. It's a title reserved for indigenous people, and POC. I know what you're thinking, "But it's so cute and perfect!". That's what I thought too. I didn't even know it wasn't for white people until months after I first started using the term. But please, this term is not for us to use. Use one of the alternatives that have been created in the wake of this, like "princus" and "princen". Those are two perfectly acceptable terms for you to use. 

Just don't use "princex", unless you're referring to an indigenous person, or a POC. It's cultural appropriation, and it's very disrespectful. Please spread the word so we can give this term back to the people it belongs to.

And to all the indigenous and POC who have been hurt by our appropriation of your term, I'm truly very sorry. I hope that all the other white people who misused your term soon recognize the errors of their ways.

I saw Muzzy at a grocery store yesterday. I told him how cool it was to meet him in person, but I didn't want to be a douche and bother him and ask him for photos or anything.
He said, "Oh, like you're doing now?"
I was taken aback, and all I could say was "Huh?" but he kept cutting me off and going "huh? huh? huh?" and closing his paws shut in front of my face. I walked away and continued with my shopping, and I heard him chuckle as I walked off. When I came to pay for my stuff up front I saw him trying to walk out the doors with like fifteen clocks in his hands without paying.
The girl at the counter was very nice about it and professional, and was like "Sir, you need to pay for those first." At first he kept pretending to be tired and not hear her, but eventually turned back around and brought them to the counter.
When she took one of the clocks and started scanning it multiple times, he stopped her and told her to scan them each individually "to prevent any electrical infetterence," and then turned around and winked at me. Hey everyone.

You already know that Facebook has been deleting a number of pages for arbitrary reasons and since there's virtually no other social media platform to jump ship to the pages that are still operational have decided to take action and hit back before we inevitably get unpublished.

This page and many others are simultaneously posting this message in order to rally fans to file FTC (Federal Trade Commission) complaints against Facebook for "fraudulent" content review policies and a misleading community guidelines. The FTC is a governmental entity that regulates private companies and protects consumers against fraud and monopoly, so let's give zucc a taste of his own medicine.

Here are the main points of our complaint:

1. Facebook claims that content has been reviewed when it clearly isn't. Graphic gore and racial hate speech routinely remains after being reported, which any reasonable reviewer would catch.

2. Verified pages appear to operate under a different set of standards, contrary to the claims made by Facebook. Pages such as tila tequila and Tess holiday for example, post nudity and offensive content that is never unpublished.

3. Facebook's statements are fraudulent and meant to pacify consumers.

We encourage all of our fans to write their own complaints against Facebook, hitting on those points and any others they might add.

The website is https://www.ftccomplaintassistant.gov/Information

-> category internet services, online shopping & computers-> internet services-> social networking services

You can fill out as much or as little information you feel necessary.

This may not make a difference, and it sounds a bit cringey, but consider it a symbolic gesture and show of solidarity among dozens of meme pages and the ironic meme community as a whole. So as much a longshot as this is you can be a part it, and honestly we need as many people as possible to participate.

status_message:
As long time fan of this game series,  I was excited when this game was announced. When I heard everyone that played it said it was shit and untrue to the others, I avoided it and never got to play. I figured it's been 7 years and the dust has settled. Upon finally playing this, I can confirm that all the negative things I've heard were true. Even as a standalone game, it's mediocre at best. It completely shits on the lore and all the world building previously established in past games. The gameplay feels clunky and some plane missions were just tedious. Dark Daxter's levels were also unnecessary and felt like they were there just for filler and to be edgy. Storywise, it made no sense and the levels weren't fun at all. The only good thing I can say about this game was the sound design was solid. Most of the voice actors sucked but the soundtrack was alright. The best part of this game was the orb pickup sound was the same as the first game. Some of the platforming was also alright but didn't compare to the older games. Overall, it was somewhat of a painful game to play that had very little good qualities. The developers obviously didn't do their research and they went on to make shovel ware games.

Final Score: 3/10
